Dashboard layout I would build
You said “several” dashboards. I agree.

Dashboard 1 — Library Ops
This is your overview.

Panels:

total library size

library size over time

artist count

album count

track count

file types breakdown

files added per day

last promotion time

external drive free space

Dashboard 2 — Ingest Quality
This is the workflow dashboard.

Panels:

albums scanned per day

pass / warn / fail over time

top failure reasons

missing albumartist count

conflicting album values count

missing date count

suspicious auth verdict count

cover-art failures

auto-fixes applied over time

Dashboard 3 — Backup Health
Panels:

last successful backup age

backup duration

bytes mirrored per run

changed files per run

rsync exit code

primary vs backup size

stale backup alert state

Dashboard 4 — Disk / Host Health
Panels:

CPU / memory

filesystem usage

HDD temperature

SMART health indicators

IO wait

mount presence for external drives

Dashboard 5 — Plex Activity
Panels:

current active streams

who is streaming now

streams over time

direct play vs transcode

bandwidth over time

top users

stream duration

live current sessions table

recent errors/log volume

Dashboard 6 — Soulseek / Nicotine Intake
Panels:

downloads completed over time

downloaded bytes over time

current queue size

failures/timeouts

ingest source volume by day

recently completed acquisitions

This last one depends on what Nicotine logs expose cleanly, but it is still worth doing.


